txei-ipc/txei driver

DEVICES:
misc: /dev/txei -  heci interface
misc: /dev/txeimm - memory pool interface


COMPILATION TARGETS: poll, irq, si

 * make si   ->  produces driver for silicon (default)
 * make poll ->  produces default driver for FGPA/VBox with polling mode
 * make irq  ->  produces driver for FPGA/VBox with irq support
 * make x0   ->  produces driver for X0 system with w/o for MSI mapping


 * default and all -> si (vbox support this configuration)
 * make TRACE=y - enable excessive print outs
 * make DEBUG=n - disable verbose debug output

INSTALLATION:
 * run in root privileged make install
   - (e.g) sudo make install
 * NOTE: no need to install in development work mode

LOADING:
 * modprobe txei
 * (DEVELOPMENT MODE) ./scripts/reload.sh - unload (if loaded) and load the driver

REMOVING
 * modprobe -r txei
 * (DEVELOPMENT MODE) ./scripts/unload.sh

MODULE PARAMETERS:
 * dmapool=nn[KMG] - size of dmapool (physical memory reserved for dma: default (4M))

INFO: (debugfs)

 * <debugfs>/txei/meclients - GUIDS with information (./scripts/meclinets.sh)
 * <debugfs>/txei/aliveness - Aliveness status (./scripts/aliveness.sh)
 * <debugfs>/txei/mestate   - State Machine state (./scripts/mestate.sh)
 * debug messages are displayed in dmesg or /var/log/messages

DEVELOPMENT SCRIPTS:
 * ./scripts/checkpatch.pl - style check script
 * ./scripts/load.sh
 * ./scripts/unload.sh
 * ./scripts/reload.sh
